cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper focuses on Vision-to-Language problems, which are primarily related to computer vision. 
2. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper deals with incorporating high-level semantic concepts into the CNN-RNN approach for V2L problems, which is related to natural language processing. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a method to improve the state-of-the-art performance in image captioning and visual question answering, which are AI-related tasks. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses CNNs and RNNs, which are machine learning techniques, and proposes a method to incorporate high-level concepts into them. 
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper discusses the use of external semantic information to improve performance, which is related to information retrieval.
